      <back>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>No date has been preserved within the inscription, but it has been dated to the
               second half of the fourth century CE on the strength of other factors. The tombstone
               is one of about 700 discovered in Byzantine Zoora. The majority of the Greek
               tombstones from this location have been identified as Christian. The editorr notes
               that the name Ὀλεφος appears elsewhere at Ghor es-Safi.</p>
         </div>
